    "Management": {
      "text": "Treat as STEMI until ruled out\nAnticoagulation\nmay be required until wall motion abnormalities resolve\nMonitor QTc intervals and arrhythmias\nStop all QT prolonging drugs\nReplete\nmagnesium\nManagement of differs from usual\ncardiogenic shock\n[5]\nIVF\nWith LVOT obstruction, avoid volume depletion and vasodilator therapy such as nitroglycerine (similar to\nhypertrophic cardiomyopathy\nmanagement)\nInotropic medications may worsen hypotension whereas pure vasoconstriction with phenylephrine can improve MAPs\nConsider\nbeta blockers\nand\nACE inhibitors\n, which reduce recurrence\nIntra-aortic balloon pump or\nECMO\nin refractory cases",
